item.title: Cassie add a quote by Soren Kierkegaard
item.description: "The function of prayer is not to influence God, but rather to change the nature of the one who prays." -- Soren Kierkegaard

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "All language is but a poor translation." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "A book must be the axe for the frozen sea within us." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Jean-Paul Sartre
item.description: "Man is condemned to be free; because once thrown into the world, he is responsible for everything he does. It is up to you to give [life] a meaning." -- Jean-Paul Sartre

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Jean-Paul Sartre
item.description: "Everything has been figured out, except how to live." -- Jean-Paul Sartre

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Friedrich Nietzsche
item.description: "You must have chaos within you to give birth to a dancing star." -- Friedrich Nietzsche

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Friedrich Nietzsche
item.description: "Whoever fights monsters should see to it that in the process he does not become a monster. And if you gaze long enough into an abyss, the abyss will gaze back into you." -- Friedrich Nietzsche

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Rumi
item.description: "Your task is not to seek for love, but merely to seek and find all the barriers within yourself that you have built against it." -- Rumi

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Franz Kafka
item.description: "You do not need to leave your room. Remain sitting at your table and listen. Do not even listen, simply wait, be quiet, still and solitary. The world will freely offer itself to you to be unmasked, it has no choice, it will roll in ecstasy at your feet." -- Franz Kafka

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Zeno
item.description: "The reason why we have two ears and only one mouth is that we may listen the more and talk the less." -- Zeno

item.title: Cassie add a quote by Ludwig Wittgenstein
item.description: "Whereof one cannot speak, thereof one must be silent." -- Ludwig Wittgenstein
